sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  participant A as Alice (org A)
  participant RA as Rendezvous A
  participant RB as Rendezvous B (Bob's home)
  participant DB as Mailbox store (ciphertext only)
  participant B as Bob (offline → online)

  A->>RA: envelope for K_B (ratchet-enc, header-enc, signed)
  RA->>RB: federated route (mTLS)
  RB->>RB: K_B has no connected device
  RB->>DB: store blob — TTL 14d, quota-checked,<br/>type is Vec of bytes: no-serde lint enforced
  RB-->>A: queued receipt (via RA)
  Note over DB: admin view (threat A7): sizes,<br/>timestamps, opaque blobs — nothing else

  alt quota exceeded
    RB-->>A: mailbox full — surfaced to SENDER
  else TTL expiry
    DB->>DB: purge on schedule (clock-advance tested)
  end

  B->>RB: WSS connect + identity-key auth
  RB->>DB: drain for K_B
  DB-->>B: envelopes (possibly out of order)
  Note over B: dedup by envelope id ·<br/>skipped-message keys handle reordering
  B-->>RB: per-envelope ACK
  RB->>DB: delete on acknowledged delivery
  Note over RB,DB: TTL=0 org config ⇒ store genuinely disabled —<br/>pure-P2P delivery mode
